 Usage instructions

This workflow is designed to migrate and patch a database to a new home that has been put in place. The database should be managed by Oracle Grid Infrastructure. The workflow will work for both Grid Standalone and Grid Cluster environments. The workflow is a database level workflow so you can migrate each database individually. 
 Worfklow Use Cases

 Migration after Oracle - Oracle - Patch Grid Infrastructure and Databases is run with "2 Phase Patching" set to True

When running the workflow after "2 Phase Patching" you will not need to specify the new Oracle Home that you are migrating to since the previous workflow will have left artefacts to guide the next workflow for a 2 phase patching approach.\:

|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|New Oracle Home |  |

 Migrating manually to new Oracle Home installed by other manual process

This use case can be used if the Oracle Home you are migrating to was not setup by the dma workflow "Oracle - Patch Grid Infrastructure and Databases"\:
|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|New Oracle Home | /u01/app/oracle/product/11.2/new_home_1 |


 Results verification

To further verify the results\:

\# Log in to the target server.
\# cat /etc/oratab and run srvctl config database -d databasename to verify the new home you database is running in.


 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Database Name - No description
    Instance Name - No description
    Oracle Home - No description
    Oracle OS User - No description
    Oracle Version - Version of the Oracle Installation.
    Server.Become Routine - No description
    Server.Name - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    New Oracle Home - Optional\: Oracle Home of new patched Oracle Home you want to migrate the database to.
    Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: A comma-separated list of Oracle errors to be ignored when applying the patch to the database. This is in addition to the list of Oracle errors specified in the patch readme. Values are of the form ORA-nnnnn. Example\: ORA-04020,ORA-03113
